      <description>Joyce Robinson was a librarian at Harding Elementary School in
            Scotlandville, La., during the crossover of East Baton Rouge Parish public school
            teachers between white and black schools in 1970. She served as a liaison for the new
            teachers arriving at Harding Elementary.</description>
